  "doc_id": "31767",
  "text": "This MQL system includes an atomizer, a cutting fluid carrier, a discharge nozzle. The atomizer operates as an injector in which high-pressure air is used to atomize the coolant. The atomized cooling is sent to the air handling zone in a low-pressure distribution system [CITATION_1] . Due to the venturi effect in the mixing chamber, the partial vacuum-absorbs the cutting fluid in the oil reservoir and is held here at a constant hydraulic load. The air passing through the mixing chamber atomizes the stream of cooling fluid into the aerosol of micron-sized particles. If this aerosol cutter is sprayed in mist, it works as lubricant as the cooling medium and penetrates the depths of the tool-workpiece interface.",
